Hey other nail artists, do you feel like some days you're just another cog in the capitalism/pollution machine? Yeah.. me too. 

I have such a huge issue with fast fashion and major corporations and their carbon emissions that I can't help but also realize what a huge role we all play in the problem. 

Like, I'm grateful to this industry for helping me out of another worse one, but I still don't feel like I'm at peace with what I do. I love getting to create and express myself artistically through #nails but im all too aware of the negative enviromental impact our industry has. 

Beauty products and fashion are 3rd on the list of largest polluting industries on earth. That's saying that our industry pollutes more than all transport like cars/boats/trains. 😨 

This isn't me saying I'm quitting because at this moment, the fuck else am I gonna do? But I just wanted to open up about how I feel since I'm all over ig denouncing things like big oil, billionaires and major corporations (owned by billionaires) 

I'm not blind to the conflict of interest. I feel it deeply and I struggle with it every day I work. 

Do you think the beauty industry will have a place in the grim environmental nightmare of a future we have in store? 

Happy Thursday 😅
